name: Acolyte - Yule
description: The Yule are self-proclaimed protectors of the laws of The Order, and are allowed to hunt down rebels and malcontents only because the rest of wizard-kind fear their near-religious zeal.

name: Acolyte - Vagabond
description: Not all wizards are comfortable within the confines of The Order, and while not necessarily traitors, some vagabonds nevertheless find themselves roaming the wilds and consorting with chaotic creatures.

name: Bogwitch - Druid
description: Amongst the most powerful creatures of The Coven, the Bogwitches are nature's fury given shape, welding hateful spells against anyone who dares threaten the balance of magic.

name: Acolyte - Gameroos
description: Wizards of The Order are creatures of rank and law, and those who are too flamboyant are harshly reprimanded. Nevertheless, some wizards can't help but to show off, defiantly demonstrating their individuality.

name: Acolyte - Arbiter
description: Judges and spies, an Arbiter of The Order uses whatever means they deem necessary to sniff out corruption and dissidents. Through subterfuge, extortion and magic, no secrets are safe for long.

name: Acolyte - Outcast
description: Disillusioned or discontent, a wizard might choose to leave The Order, either voluntarily or cast out. Either way, the result is the same; an Outcast can never return, and will be hunted by their old allies for sport.

name: Bogwitch - Enthralled
description: A Bogwitch captured by The Order can be branded and “tamed” with malicious magics. Forces of nature taken shape, the brands on the Enthralled direct their fury and hatred towards enemies of The Order.

name: Acolyte - Aigey
description: Wizards of The Order are creatures of rank and law, and those who are too flamboyant are harshly reprimanded. Nevertheless, some wizards can't help but to show off, defiantly demonstrating their individuality.

name: Acolyte - Tomte
description: Mercurial spirits that take humanoid shape during the winter seasons, the Tomte travels the world to punish the wicked and reward the just according to some mad list of names that they check twice.

name: Acolyte - Archon
description: The pinnacle of wizardkind, at least according to the Order. No wizard can hope to aspire any higher within the order, at least not without resorting to forbidden and soul-shattering magic.

name: Bogwitch - Firbog
description: Some bogwitches are so consumed by their burning fury that it explodes out of their chest, literally. These hateful spirits burn their own life force as fuel for destructive magics to torch enemies of the Coven.

name: Acolyte - Custodian
description: Pragmatic and fearless, the wizards that guard the shrines of hard-to-survive places like the Cauldron has long since adopted a stoic attitude towards searing flames, molten lava and missing eyebrows.

name: Acolyte - Chronicler
description: Those who dedicate their lives in pursuit of knowledge often end up thriving in Codex, the pocket dimension of hidden lore, as long as they can avoid the gaze of the the things that lurk therein.

name: Bogwitch - Cherry Blossom
description: Some of the spirits and wizards of the Coven draw magic from the changing seasons and adorn their garb according to the current one, though some instead change the season according to their garb.

name: Bogwitch - Autumn Dancer
description: In an attempt to save what is left of the world, some spirits of the Coven dedicate themselves to preserving places with untouched magic energies, and ritually, and brutally, punish anyone who trespass.

name: Overgrown
description: Every wizard is a wellspring of magical energies that they have harvested, and while most wizards feel it is their right, The Coven feels strongly that those energies be returned to the world, willing or not.

name: Arcane Capture
description: The act of capturing a soul is both used as punishment and to collect trophies from fallen adversaries. It's a crude method, if only because of lack of test subjects for refining the process.

name: Repository
description: If knowledge is power, some wizards reason that books, as knowledge made manifest, must be power in physical form. How to harness this power has yet to be discovered however, despite years of testing.

name: Bookshelf
description: If knowledge is the life-blood of a wizard, and the staff is an extension of a wizard's will, surely the combination of the two is the epitome of arcane research.

name: Caged
description: Wizards of all times has always been keeping familiars to assist with spellcasting and research. When The Order started falling into madness, fewer familiars stayed voluntarily.

name: Candelabrum
description: Threading through dimensions of endless libraries, few things terrify a wizard as much as being unable to read an arcane tome for lack of light. This device allows a wizard to breath easy in any dimness.

name: Cornivorous
description: Some brilliant practitioners of the schools of life magic keep pushing the boundaries of magic potential and sensibility. Though impressive, few of these wizards live past their first new “discoveries”.

name: Hanged Man
description: Sometimes, the remains of a heretic is kept not as a punishment for their soul, but as a gruesome reminder to everyone else that final death await anyone who disobey The Order.

name: Left Hand Path
description: While near-impossible to contain, a captive demon has many uses, and their hands are a great aid in spellcasting as long as it is well cared for and kept out of strangling reach.

name: Iron Tipped
description: While wrapping a staff in iron does little to increase its arcane conductivity, it does absolutely everything for its electrical conductivity. Many wizards realize this only after carrying it through a thunderstorm.

name: Old Prisoner
description: Prisoners to The Order are kept under lock and key for the duration of their imprisonment, although their punishment is often a lot longer than merely a life sentence.

name: Reliquary
description: The remains of powerful beings and ancient wizards are sometimes honored and kept as a tribute to their importance, or more commonly, as a trophy for the wizard who finally took them down.

name: Rocking
description: As a tribute to the most powerful spell of wizardkind, only the most powerful wizard has the physical endurance to carry this idol made out of hundreds of pounds of non-magical stone.

name: Skeletal
description: Some wizards claim that the skull of ancient wizards or other powerful beings can act as advisors and tutors, but their insane babbling about skulls often make them pariahs amongst their peers.

name: Soul Wrapped
description: Even after their rival has perished, some wizards have trouble letting go of the enmity, to the point of bringing the soul of their departed foe back and brandishing it as a morbid, if ornate, trophy.

name: Conductor
description: While electricity is of little interest to most wizards, a few eccentric ones study this non-magical force as an alternative, accessible energy source, despite being ridiculed by their peers for their naive goals.

name: Thorns
description: Those that travel outside the confines of the holds and towers of The Order know the dangers that the heathens of The Coven pose, and why so few wizards travel outside their confines.

name: Candy Cane
description: Whatever madness drives a Tomte often infects the world around it, creating eldritch formations of solidified glucose around the realm. While unnerving and sticky, they work well as arcane conductors.

name: Yule Branch
description: The Yule order often take it upon themselves to protect the world from the Tomte threat, and often dress small branches of evergreen with arcane baubles in order to ward the spirits off.

name: Longstaff
description: Tried, tested and true, a long piece of wood is the most common variant of the arcane conductor, both assisting with spellcasting and with supporting aged wizards in their upright position.

name: Overlord
description: Most wizards come to a point in their careers in which their feeling of superiority outgrow their loyalty to The Order. Grandiose but short-lived, these wizards often lean too heavily on unreliable minions.

name: Firekeeper
description: Leftover energies from spellcasting can cause a build-up of chaotic magic, and rather than suffering horrific mutations, many wizards choose to burn off the excessive energies through various devices.

name: Icicle
description: Drawing on the leftover magical energies of spellcasting, many wizards form and carry elaborate sculptures of ice to showcase their aptitude with magic, rather than actually practicing conservation.

name: Death Toll
description: A favorite amongst the Yule, the sonorous tones of the bell makes sure that everyone expects the impending inquisition, despite popular belief of the contrary.

name: Crucible
description: Through gimbals of arcane metals, the souls of powerful creatures can be contained and materialized. While it doesn't improve spellcasting in any way, the cosmetic value is indisputable.

name: Splinter
description: Popular amongst the naturalistic spellcasters of The Coven and wizards in a hurry alike, availability sometimes takes priority over form and design when it comes to choosing the proper staff.

name: Marrow
description: Any staff can be used as an arcane conductor, but many wizards put great faith in post-living materials with their naturally formed hollow canals, and swear by their efficiency for certain types of magic.

name: Dreamcatcher
description: Creating a Dreamcatcher is a simple task for any wizard, but special care must be made to include a container powerful enough to store even a passing nightmare if it is to be of any use.

name: Far-Fetched
description: Artificers that channel their magic through objects often keep a staff around to remind them of their humble beginnings as mere tinkerers and inventors of world-altering devices.

name: Iron Brand
description: The implement of control and punishment, wizards carrying this tool is feared and respected within The Order, while they are hunted and destroyed on sight by those outside.

name: Memento
description: Taking trophies from fallen enemies is a time-honored tradition among wizards, but some remains expire sooner than others. Encapsulated in ice however, even eldritch spoils can be kept indefinitely.

name: Truthspeaker
description: While the words spoken by this captive demon is always inarguably true, it has yet to utter one single phrase that wasn't a litany of vulgarities or well-placed insults, made worse by their accuracy.

name: Equinox Branch
description: Some wizards are obsessed with hatching the mysterious Equinox eggs, painting them and even going so far as to dress up as colourful mammals in an odd ritual to bring forth what is sleeping inside.

name: Equinox Scepter
description: The mysterious eggs that appears during the Equinox are hunted down and collected by wizards of all kinds. While none ever hatch, they are rumoured to contain everything from legendary birds to chocolate.

name: Time Capsule
description: For those who have mastered the arts of temporal magic, keeping track of time is essential to make sure you don’t end up killing your past self in the belief that they are an impostor.

name: Effigy
description: It's not known if the Effigy wielded by the insane firbogs are simple constructs, or if they are the last burning remains of another firbog. Regardless, the hateful fire that flows through burns everything to ash.

name: Spinefall
description: In a world where magic is power, physical violence is not frowned-upon as much as it is a nearly forgotten concept. Some creative wizards has taken it upon themselves to reintroduce it as a part of their rhetoric.

name: Triangle
description: Even the calculus-obsessed mathemancers of the order needs tools for their equations and experiments, and while they claim to understand the fundamentals of magic and reality, they still resort to the staff to lean on.

name: Bent
description: Wizards that escape captivity sometimes bend the bars and chains of their prison into a symbol of their freedom, highlighting the question ‘Why the blazes did we think bars and chains would hold a wizard?’

name: Banner Gatekeeper
description: While often vain and self-centered, some wizards of the order nevertheless carry banners and heraldry to proclaim their allegiance, whether to intimidate, brag, or simply because the colours look good.

name: Ignis Faatus
description: Strange blue lights have been the stuff of legend for generations, and while the lantern definitely is useful for luring enemies to their doom in misty swamps, the wizards of the Coven mostly use it as a light source.

name: Pythagoras
description: For some wizards, magic is a science as much as an art form, and they turn to calculations and equations to solve the questions of reality, caring little that the questions themselves actually change the world.

name: Shatter
description: When a shooting star explodes, it is not uncommon for a master of kinetics to halt the explosion mid-blow and shape it into a staff of suppressed arcane energies. Elegant, as long as they don’t lose concentration.

name: Banner Seeker
description: While often vain and self-centered, some wizards of the order nevertheless carry banners and heraldry to proclaim their allegiance, whether to intimidate, brag, or simply because the colours look good.

name: Bouquet
description: While the flowers are said to be able to control the minds of lesser beings, wizards who carry the flowers keep repeating that they are fine, over and over again as they plant new seeds with a religious zeal.

name: Cleansweep
description: Every wizard starts from the bottom as an apprentice to a more powerful sorcerer, and more often than not, even simple tasks such as mopping the floors can turn into a flood of magical disaster.

name: Mandragora
description: The pods of the mandragora plant have evolved to look like toothy jaws to scare off predators, and the circle of dark druids assures us that while valuable, does not actually bite or digest fingers and limbs.

name: Banner Rebirth
description: The wizards and creatures of the Coven care little for heraldry and the display of colours, though they take a morbid pride in branding the remains of their enemies and carrying them as warnings to others.

name: Gallows
description: While hanging is a pointless punishment for anyone who can wave their hands and fly, it is still widely used for symbolic reasons, even if the convicted often starve to death before the neck snaps.

name: Schism
description: While conflicts within the order are as common as the number of wizards in the order, sometimes a new idea spark such controversy and debate that they must be preserved as they were presented.

name: Crossroads
description: There is always a risk of becoming lost while traversing the different roads, natural and unnatural alike, that a wizard must walk, and the wisest bring something along to guide the way.

name: Banner Divide
description: The wizards and creatures of the Coven care little for heraldry and the display of colours, though they take a morbid pride in branding the remains of their enemies and carrying them as warnings to others.

name: Bogwitch - Forged
description: Not even death means freedom for those nature spirits that are captured by the Order. With their bodies gone, their souls are imprisoned inside magical constructs, and in a cruel twist their burning hate for wizards is used as a source of power for the construct.

name: Acolyte - Aurumancer
description: Jokingly known as the Order's accountants, these wizards keep track of every debt, favor and slight within the Order. With their knack for both fate and time magic however, one should know that "lateness fees" can be collected in actual days and hours of lifetime, and that "deadline" is rather literal.

name: Acolyte - Awakened
description: Spirits are sometimes used as power sources for a wizard's enchantment, and one must take care to keep those spirits in check. Too many powerful spirits can band together when a wizard is weakened or distracted, and form a new entity bent on bringing down all wizard-kind. With any luck, the wizard dies quickly rather than being dragged around by the neck by their own cloak of power.

name: Acolyte - Wickerman
description: Sometimes when a wizard is burned in effigy, their wicker counterpart takes a twisted life of their own. These Wickermen usually take only the most heinous characteristics of the original wizard, and are used as evidence of said wizard's flaws in every debate.

name: Acolyte - Gingerbeard
description: These fierce guardians of the Order are so feared and respected amongst the common folk that some peasants adopted a tradition of baking their likeness into sweetbread, that was used as tribute during their annual heretic hunts.

name: Fruity
description: "The Apple of Life" is probably the most dangerously misnamed artifacts of the Order. The mere touch of this apple cause branches, vines and fruit to grow sprout at impossible speeds, burrowing into the ground or any nearby object or person.

name: Executioner
description: Despite it's use as a tool of execution, the blade of this weapon is surprisingly blunt, as the runes of transportation on the blade actually cause the blade to separate time and space wherever it cuts. Used on a wizard's neck, the similarities with an actual sharp blade is uncanny.

name: Flask
description: This eldritch device takes the dying breath of a wizard's enemy and filters it through water to create a disturbing yet refreshing beverage. If broken, it can also be used as a fairly sharp spear.
